<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-39-1173 </DOCNO><TEXT>By ion-beam mixing, amorphization of Ni-Zr thin films has been studiedin the temperature range 77-673 K for various compositions. Microstructureswere characterized by TEM. The results are compared with correspondingdata obtained by use of melt-spinning and solid-state amorphization reactions,and with results of ion-beam mixing of the systems Fe-Zr and Co-Zr. 13refs.; 1 figure.</TEXT></DOC>